                            <comment id="13044611" author="srowen" created="Sun, 5 Jun 2011 20:19:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree, this is over half the test time and does burn a fair bit of time as I run tests frequently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One way to speed it up is to shrink the test data size, no? I did so and made it run about 3x faster without causing it to fail, but does this look like it remains a valid test?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The non-CLI test can be shrunk further but then an assertion about the size of error fails.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13045349" author="hudson" created="Tue, 7 Jun 2011 11:05:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #872 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/872/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/872/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-690&quot; title=&quot;LanczosSolver tests take forever.  No fun.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-690&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-690&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; reduce test input size to speed up test&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;srowen : &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/?root=Apache-SVN&amp;amp;view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1132893&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/?root=Apache-SVN&amp;amp;view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1132893&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Files : &lt;/p&gt;
